PhoenixDKIM 1.0.0-beta3 release notes
======================================

Date: 4 June 2026


Metrics and observability
--------------------------

  - MetricsFile: Prometheus textfile exporter — PhoenixDKIM writes a
    Prometheus-format counters file to the node_exporter textfile collector
    directory; no extra library or daemon required.  Switched on by setting
    MetricsFile in phoenixdkim.conf.
  - StatsDHost: UDP StatsD exporter — send counters to a StatsD/Graphite
    endpoint.
  - LogResults: emit a structured per-message log line with signing /
    verification outcome, algorithm, key size, and domain.
  - systemd unit gains ReadWritePaths= for the MetricsFile directory.


Build
------

  - Accept Lua >= 5.4 (not exactly 5.4); fixes builds on distributions
    shipping Lua 5.5 (e.g. Fedora Rawhide).


Website
--------

  - Documentation guides in docs/ are now rendered into the website and served
    as the authoritative reference (Quick Start, Key Rotation, Removed
    Features, Crypto Policy, Multisigning, Metrics).
  - Website build now warns on dead internal links.


Debian packaging
-----------------

  - Fix dpkg-gencontrol substvar warnings: phoenixdkim-keygen (Perl script)
    now depends on ${perl:Depends}; phoenixdkim-tools drops stray
    ${perl:Depends} and ${python3:Depends}.
  - Gate libbsd-dev on Debian 12 and earlier via
    "libc6-dev (>= 2.38) | libbsd-dev" — not needed on Trixie+ where
    strlcpy/strlcat are in glibc.


Documentation
--------------

  - DKIM2 readiness tracker added to docs.
  - README: table of contents, packages and ports section, build dependency
    clarifications.
